## Why are we doing this work

We want to add an `issueLinks` field to the `PipelineSecurityReportFinding` GraphQL type for use in the new security finding modals. This can also take an argument for the link type.

Example of new query:

```graphql
query {
  project(fullPath:"<project path>") {
    pipeline(iid:"<pipeline iid>") {
      securityReportFinding(uuid:"<uuid>") {
        issueLinks 
          nodes {
            id
            issue {
              <issue data>
            }
            linkType
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Response data will be [`vulnerabilityType.issueLinks`](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/api/graphql/reference/#vulnerabilityissuelink) and the issue data defined by the [`Issue` type](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/api/graphql/reference/#issue)

Note that this differs from the [original discussion](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/382913#3-issue-notes "Spike: Investigate and capture options on how to integrate, deploy and iterate the GraphQL version of the modal") in the spike. While the spike requests the existing vulnerability feedback data, this will more closely align with the current GraphQL implementation.

This also require implementing the new vulnerability promotion implementation for issue creation from the REST API. Otherwise we will have a bug where issues get created but not linked through the vulnerabilities.

